===Etymology===
From [[Mag]], a nickname for [[Margaret]] that was used to denote a [[chatterer]], and [[pie#Etymology_2|pie]], an archaic word meaning "magpie".

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈmæɡˌpaɪ/}}, {{SAMPA|/"m{g%paI/}}
* {{hyphenation|mag|pie}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# One of several kinds of [[bird]] in the family ''Corvidae'', especially ''Pica pica''.
# A superficially similar Australian bird, ''Gymnorhina tibicen.''
# Someone who displays a magpie-like quality such as collecting, or committing robbery.
# {{slang}} Fan or member of [[w:Newcastle United F.C|Newcastle United FC]].

